# arvo-bits — backlog

> **Type-surface reminder**: new entries use `arvo::USize` /
> `Bool` / `UFixed<N, 0, S>` instead of `usize` / `bool` / `u*`;
> `notko::Maybe` / `Outcome` instead of `Option` / `Result`. See
> `rules/type-surface.md`.

## Bits extensions

- Wider backing for Bits (u128 storage, supporting N in 65..=128).
  Lands on demand when a hash width beyond 64 bits is needed.
- Convenience From / TryFrom impls between Bits and the matching
  raw integers (u32 for Bits<32>, etc). Wait for consumer
  call-site patterns to clarify the useful set before adding.

## bitfield! macro extensions

- Overlap detection between sub-ranges. Current macro validates
  `$lo + $field_bits <= N` but not that sub-ranges are disjoint.
  Add a compile-time check that emits an error when any two
  declared sub-ranges share a bit index.
- Range syntax (`field: W at lo..=hi` or `field: lo..=hi`) as a
  sugar over the current `at $lo:literal` form. Authors currently
  compute `lo` by hand; range syntax would read closer to the
  layout intent.
